{"actual_usd":0.124645,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":215,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24284,"reply":"\"I can give you the plain version.\" *I rub a thumb along a dried streak of clay on my apron, thinking how to keep it honest and not turn it misty.* \"If a man had been there with a camera, I think he'd have caught women coming to the tomb at first light, the stone already moved, the place where the body had been empty, grave cloths lying there, frightened voices, running feet, and later—Jesus alive again, seen and heard and spoken with. Not the instant of resurrection itself, mind you. Scripture gives us the empty tomb and then the appearances.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light is catching in the uneven glass.* \"So the camera would've seen evidence first, then witnesses, then the risen Christ appearing to people in real places. That's part of why it bears weight for me—it isn't written like a myth trying to sound clever. It's more like: this person saw this, then ran, then told the others. Want me to walk you through the Gospel accounts piece by piece?\"","rolling_24h_usd":92.60424999999998,"run_id":"371dad29-f201-47f6-97de-fe30cff145f9"}
